The Premier League have released Manchester City’s 25-man squad for the 2019/2020 season. Squads were confirmed ahead of the first game of the season, but have just been released now, following the closure of the European transfer window on Monday. The 25-man squad system was introduced at the start of the 2010/2011 season. Squads cannot include more than 17 non-homegrown players, with eight members of the team having to be developed in England. Manchester City squad list: Aguero Del Castillo, Sergio
Bravo Munoz, Claudio Andres
Carson, Scott Paul*
